goodwill and other intangibles when calculating TCE.
Key performance measures
Core loans is considered a key performance measure. Core
loans represents loans considered central to the Firm’s ongoing
businesses, and excludes loans classified as trading assets,
runoff portfolios, discontinued portfolios and portfolios the
Firm has an intent to exit. Core loans is a measure utilized by
the Firm and its investors and analysts in assessing actual
growth in the loan portfolio.
