Net income was $2.8 billion, a decrease of 1%.
Net revenue was $14.3 billion, an increase of 2%. Net interest
income was $3.5 billion, down 1%, driven by deposit margin
compression, predominantly offset by loan and deposit growth.
Noninterest revenue was $10.8 billion, up 3%, driven by
higher net investment valuation gains and growth in fees on
higher average market levels, partially offset by a shift in the
mix toward lower fee products.
