to the resolution of certain tax audits. The prior year expense
reflected a net benefit of $302 million resulting from changes
in estimates under the TCJA related to the remeasurement of
certain deferred taxes and the deemed repatriation tax on non-
U.S. earnings, which was more than offset by changes to
certain tax reserves and other tax adjustments.
