portion of the Firm’s deposits are consumer deposits and
wholesale operating deposits, which are both considered to be
stable sources of liquidity. Wholesale operating deposits are
considered to be stable sources of liquidity because they are
generated from customers that maintain operating service
relationships with the Firm.
