selection of countries represents the Firm’s largest total
exposures by country, based on the Firm’s internal country risk
management approach, and does not represent the Firm’s view
of any actual or potentially adverse credit conditions.
Country exposures may fluctuate from period to period due to
client activity and market flows. The increase in exposure in
Japan is largely due to increased cash balances placed with the
central bank of Japan, driven by client activity. 
