involvement includes servicing the loans, holding senior interests or subordinated interests (including amounts required to be held
pursuant to credit risk retention rules), recourse or guarantee arrangements, and derivative contracts. In certain instances, the Firm’s
only continuing involvement is servicing the loans. The Firm’s maximum loss exposure from retained and purchased interests is the
