Note 29 – Pledged assets and collateral
Pledged assets
The Firm pledges financial assets that it owns to maintain
potential borrowing capacity at discount windows with Federal
Reserve banks, various other central banks and FHLBs.
Additionally, the Firm pledges assets for other purposes,
including to collateralize repurchase and other securities
financing agreements, to cover short sales and to collateralize
derivative contracts and deposits. Certain of these pledged
assets may be sold or repledged or otherwise used by the
secured parties and are parenthetically identified on the
Consolidated balance sheets as assets pledged.
