Provided below is a summary of JPMorgan Chase’s
consolidated average balances, interest and rates on a taxable-
equivalent basis for the years 2017 through 2019. Income
computed on a taxable-equivalent basis is the income reported
in the Consolidated statements of income, adjusted to present interest income and rates earned on assets
exempt from income taxes (i.e., federal taxes) on a basis
comparable with other taxable investments. The incremental
tax rate used for calculating the taxable-equivalent adjustment
was approximately 24% in both 2019 and 2018, and 37% in
2017.
