respectively.
(b)Included on the Consolidated balance sheets in beneficial interests issued by consolidated VIEs.
Federal funds purchased represent overnight funds. Securities loaned or sold under repurchase agreements generally mature
between one and ninety days. Commercial paper generally is issued in amounts not less than $100,000, and with maturities of 270
days or less. Other borrowed funds consist of demand notes, term federal funds purchased, and various other borrowings that
generally have maturities of one year or less.
